cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the development of an AutoML solution for scenarios in which data distribution changes relatively slowly over time, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of concept drift detection techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
